@@ -0,0 +1,106 @@
+# Implementation Summary: Drop Support for ktlint-disable/ktlint-enable Directives
+
+## Changes Made
+
+### 1. Created New Migration Rule
+- **File**: `ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/main/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/rules/KtlintDirectiveToSuppressionRule.kt`
+- **Purpose**: Detects legacy ktlint-disable/ktlint-enable directive comments and suggests migration to @Suppress annotations
+- **Features**:
+  - Detects EOL comments: `// ktlint-disable rule-name`
+  - Detects block comments: `/* ktlint-disable rule-name */` and `/* ktlint-enable rule-name */`
+  - Normalizes experimental rule references to standard rules
+  - Provides specific suggestions for @Suppress annotation format
+  - Does not auto-correct (warns only) to avoid complex PSI manipulation
+
+### 2. Removed Old Directive Support
+- **File**: `ktlint-rule-engine/src/main/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/rule/engine/internal/SuppressionLocatorBuilder.kt`
+- **Changes**:
+  - Removed comment suppression processing entirely
+  - Removed `createSuppressionHintFromComment()` methods
+  - Removed `CommentSuppressionHint` class and related utilities
+  - Kept only `@Suppress` annotation processing
+  - Cleaned up unused imports
+
+### 3. Updated Existing Rules
+- **File**: `ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/main/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/rules/NoSingleLineBlockCommentRule.kt`
+  - Removed special handling for ktlint suppression directives in block comments
+  - Removed `isKtlintSuppressionDirective()` method and TODO comment
+- **File**: `ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/main/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/rules/MaxLineLengthRule.kt`
+  - Removed special exemption for `// ktlint-disable` comments from line length checks
+
+### 4. Added New Rule to Ruleset
+- **File**: `ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/main/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/StandardRuleSetProvider.kt`
+- **Changes**: Added `KtlintDirectiveToSuppressionRule` to the rule providers set
+
+### 5. Updated Tests
+- **File**: `ktlint-rule-engine/src/test/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/rule/engine/internal/SuppressionLocatorBuilderTest.kt`
+  - Updated tests to expect that old directives no longer suppress violations
+  - Converted suppression tests to show directives are ignored
+- **Multiple test files**: Updated tests that used old directives to either:
+  - Expect violations where previously suppressed
+  - Test the new behavior where applicable
+
+### 6. Created Comprehensive Test Coverage
+- **File**: `ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/test/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/rules/KtlintDirectiveToSuppressionRuleTest.kt`
+- **Tests**:
+  - EOL directive detection for all rules and specific rules
+  - Block directive detection
+  - Rule ID normalization (experimental: -> standard:)
+  - ktlint-enable directive detection
+  - Rule ID with existing namespace preservation
+
+### 7. Updated Documentation
+- **File**: `CHANGELOG.md`
+- **Changes**:
+  - Added removal notice in `### Removed` section
+  - Added new rule notice in `### Added` section
+
+## Migration Path for Users
+
+### Before (deprecated):
+```kotlin
+val foo = "foo" // ktlint-disable no-multi-spaces
+/* ktlint-disable max-line-length */
+val longVariable = "very long string that exceeds max line length"
+/* ktlint-enable max-line-length */
+```
+
+### After (recommended):
+```kotlin
+@Suppress("ktlint:standard:no-multi-spaces")
+val foo = "foo"
+@Suppress("ktlint:standard:max-line-length")
+val longVariable = "very long string that exceeds max line length"
+```
+
+### File-level suppression:
+```kotlin
+@file:Suppress("ktlint")
+// or
+@file:Suppress("ktlint:standard:specific-rule")
+```
+
+## Benefits of This Change
+
+1. **Consistency**: Uses standard Kotlin suppression mechanism
+2. **IDE Support**: Better integration with IDE inspections and refactoring tools
+3. **Scope Clarity**: @Suppress annotations clearly define their scope
+4. **Standard Compliance**: Aligns with Kotlin ecosystem best practices
+5. **Maintainability**: Removes custom suppression logic complexity
+
+## Breaking Change Notice
+
+This is a **breaking change** for version 1.0. Users must:
+1. Run the new rule to find all usage of old directives
+2. Replace them with appropriate @Suppress annotations
+3. The new rule provides specific suggestions for each case
+
+## Testing
+
+All changes include comprehensive test coverage:
+- Unit tests for the new rule
+- Updated existing tests to reflect new behavior
+- Regression tests to ensure @Suppress still works correctly
+
+The implementation preserves all existing @Suppress functionality while removing the deprecated directive support.
+

